WEBVTT

00:09.125 --> 00:11.958
NETFLIX PRESENTS

01:31.750 --> 01:33.542
-Let me get it, Mom.
-I got it.

01:34.375 --> 01:35.208
Sit down.

01:36.458 --> 01:37.750
Come on, sit down.

01:37.833 --> 01:41.167
I told you not to work so hard.
You end up like this.

01:41.250 --> 01:42.750
I have to work.

01:43.542 --> 01:45.125
Hand me the gift bag.

01:48.792 --> 01:50.833
I got you a little something.

01:53.833 --> 01:54.667
Look.

01:56.333 --> 01:58.458
A new shirt for your trip.

01:59.958 --> 02:02.125
You don't need to waste money on this.

02:02.208 --> 02:03.125
Waste money?

02:03.208 --> 02:05.208
Will you travel wearing rags? No!

02:05.292 --> 02:08.583
-This is a month's worth of groceries.
-But you'll look gorgeous.

02:08.667 --> 02:10.208
Try it on.

02:10.292 --> 02:11.375
Isn't it gorgeous?

02:11.917 --> 02:13.542
-It is.
-It's really nice.

02:13.625 --> 02:14.667
It is.

02:14.750 --> 02:16.417
Look, there's more.

02:18.458 --> 02:19.333
<i>Dona </i>Ana…

02:20.583 --> 02:21.417
Right?

02:22.042 --> 02:23.750
You can read them on your trip.

02:24.333 --> 02:25.750
You picked them, didn't you?

02:26.417 --> 02:28.708
-I did.
-What's written here?

02:29.292 --> 02:32.875
Flying-- Don't do that!

02:33.583 --> 02:35.750
Give it here. Let me put it aside.

02:36.375 --> 02:37.417
Thank you, Mom.

02:38.208 --> 02:39.250
-Shall we eat?
-Yes.

02:39.333 --> 02:40.208
Say grace.

02:42.250 --> 02:45.250
Thank you, Lord,
for the food we eat today.

02:45.750 --> 02:48.125
May Mateus have a nice trip.

02:48.208 --> 02:50.958
Protect and guide him to the right path.

02:51.542 --> 02:53.417
-So be it.
-Amen.

02:54.208 --> 02:56.750
-Hey! Shoo that cat away!
-Out!

02:56.833 --> 02:58.667
Let it be! Come here.

02:59.333 --> 03:00.833
-It wants our food.
-It does.

03:00.917 --> 03:02.583
No, you first.

03:02.667 --> 03:05.125
-Sit.
-No, you've been doing chores.

03:05.208 --> 03:07.042
Oh, Lord. I'll eat, but…

03:07.125 --> 03:08.042
Eat more. Here.

03:08.875 --> 03:10.958
-That's enough.
-No, a bit more.

03:11.042 --> 03:12.125
I'm not hungry.

03:24.792 --> 03:26.792
They're running away from you.

03:50.458 --> 03:51.708
Hey there!

03:55.250 --> 03:56.667
-Hi, Mateus.
-Hi, Gilson.

03:56.750 --> 03:58.292
-Ready, man?
-I'm ready.

03:58.375 --> 03:59.458
Great!

03:59.542 --> 04:01.250
Meet my mom and sisters.

04:01.333 --> 04:02.875
<i>Dona </i>Ana, it's a pleasure.

04:02.958 --> 04:05.208
-Mateus speaks very highly of you.
-Hello.

04:05.292 --> 04:07.875
I'll stop by sometime for a cup of coffee.

04:07.958 --> 04:10.542
-Okay.
-You'll see how things will change.

04:10.625 --> 04:13.667
Thank God, my mom never had
to pick up a hoe again.

04:14.708 --> 04:16.958
In fact, this is for you, <i>Dona </i>Ana.

04:17.792 --> 04:19.875
Great changes are really coming.

04:19.958 --> 04:21.583
This is just the beginning.

04:22.375 --> 04:23.917
I insist, <i>Dona </i>Ana.

04:28.542 --> 04:30.375
Your boy will make you proud.

04:32.458 --> 04:34.917
-Let's go, Mateus. We're late.
-Let's go.

04:35.000 --> 04:36.750
São Paulo waits for no one!

04:37.292 --> 04:38.917
-What's up?
-Hi, Mateus.

05:41.125 --> 05:43.750
How's Julia?
She must be missing you already.

05:44.333 --> 05:46.792
She is already texting me.

05:46.875 --> 05:48.292
But I won't stay long.

05:48.375 --> 05:51.625
Just long enough to make money
to build us a home here.

05:51.708 --> 05:54.250
You're crazy.
You let a woman hold you back.

05:55.292 --> 05:57.625
If it's up to me, I'll never come back.

05:57.708 --> 06:01.292
Family is everything to me.
My money is theirs.

06:01.375 --> 06:05.042
What you can't do is miss the chance
of getting out of here.

06:05.125 --> 06:07.042
-To make money, get rich.
-Yes.

06:07.625 --> 06:10.250
I go to the barber shop every single week.

06:10.333 --> 06:12.208
-That's right.
-Get some nice cologne…

06:12.875 --> 06:16.292
I'm already ugly. If I don't
clean myself up, who's gonna want me?

06:17.583 --> 06:21.375
Hang in there, kids.
We'll be in São Paulo in just five hours.

06:46.208 --> 06:47.042
Samuel.

07:11.000 --> 07:13.500
Welcome to the big city, kids.

07:13.583 --> 07:16.458
-Wake up!
-I've never seen so many cars in my life.

07:16.542 --> 07:18.542
São Paulo is cool, isn't it?

07:18.625 --> 07:20.500
Look, man!

07:20.583 --> 07:22.667
As far as the eye can see!

07:49.250 --> 07:51.208
Hey there, Mr. Luca!

07:51.292 --> 07:53.042
How are you doing?

07:53.125 --> 07:54.583
I can't complain.

07:55.375 --> 07:58.625
I brought the boys.
They're looking forward to starting.

08:02.458 --> 08:03.625
How was the trip?

08:04.375 --> 08:05.500
This is Samuel.

08:06.458 --> 08:07.292
Ezequiel.

08:08.625 --> 08:10.708
-Isaque and Mateus.
-Nice to meet you.

08:11.833 --> 08:14.958
-Where are you all from?
-Catanduva.

08:16.375 --> 08:17.708
You worked the fields?

08:18.333 --> 08:21.000
-We do a bit of everything.
-They're no slackers.

08:21.083 --> 08:21.917
Nice.

08:22.542 --> 08:23.875
Is that all, Mr. Luca?

08:24.500 --> 08:26.167
Yes, Gilson. Thank you.

08:26.250 --> 08:28.542
-I gotta go. Be well, kids.
-Thanks.

08:28.625 --> 08:29.958
-Bye, Gilson.
-Come.

08:32.250 --> 08:33.625
That's the lunchroom.

08:35.125 --> 08:36.417
Workshop's here.

08:37.625 --> 08:39.208
All this is scrap.

08:45.083 --> 08:46.708
Leave your stuff on the beds.

08:49.917 --> 08:52.458
I need your documents. Did you bring IDs?

08:53.625 --> 08:54.792
May I ask why?

08:55.458 --> 08:56.583
For the paperwork.

08:57.875 --> 08:58.875
Here, Mr. Luca.

08:59.500 --> 09:01.167
-Thanks.
-Here, Mr. Luca.

09:02.167 --> 09:03.833
Mr. Luca, and our contracts?

09:04.833 --> 09:06.667
We'll look into it this week.

09:09.208 --> 09:13.417
With all due respect, we came here
for honest work with a proper contract.

09:15.708 --> 09:17.083
I'll speak with HR.

09:18.583 --> 09:21.625
Listen up, tomorrow we got
seven deliveries to take care of.

09:22.708 --> 09:23.917
We start at 5:00 a.m.

09:24.958 --> 09:26.125
How about dinner?

09:27.500 --> 09:30.292
Gilson said all meals would be provided.

09:33.875 --> 09:35.875
They make good food down the street.

09:36.417 --> 09:37.667
Here, twenty bucks.

09:39.083 --> 09:41.208
-We start early tomorrow.
-Yes, sir.

09:41.958 --> 09:42.792
First thing.

09:44.750 --> 09:46.292
Check out those buildings.

09:47.250 --> 09:48.875
I'll buy a condo here.

09:48.958 --> 09:50.917
That one is mine. I bought it.

09:52.167 --> 09:55.000
I wanna see the city from way up high.

09:55.083 --> 09:56.167
I like that one.

09:56.250 --> 09:57.500
-Yeah.
-That's nice too.

10:03.500 --> 10:06.292
So, is everybody ready to order?

10:06.375 --> 10:07.500
-Not yet.
-Thanks.

10:09.000 --> 10:10.917
Call me when you're ready, okay?

10:13.125 --> 10:13.958
I want a steak.

10:15.333 --> 10:16.458
It's this one.

10:17.292 --> 10:19.792
-No sides?
-It's written here.

10:22.583 --> 10:23.917
It's this one, see?

10:26.083 --> 10:29.167
Steak is okay.
Should we order two and share?

10:29.250 --> 10:31.750
I don't care. I want to eat, not read.

10:33.708 --> 10:35.583
Ma'am, two steak specials.

10:35.667 --> 10:37.917
Two steak specials for four.

10:39.792 --> 10:42.708
Did you see there's open enrollment
at our school?

10:43.333 --> 10:45.833
-Maybe when I get back.
-Did you graduate?

10:46.417 --> 10:49.958
-I finished 8th grade.
-Wow! Couldn't you find a better job?

10:50.583 --> 10:52.125
There was only the fields.

10:53.708 --> 10:54.792
We met there.

10:54.875 --> 10:57.250
-We worked hard.
-Did we?

10:58.083 --> 11:00.708
We'd take twice as long
'cause he never shut up.

11:00.792 --> 11:02.250
I didn't shut up?

11:02.333 --> 11:04.708
-Yeah.
-You're the one who never shut up.

11:07.167 --> 11:09.833
How is your
<i>The Princess and the Pea </i>mattress?

11:11.292 --> 11:14.625
-Better than the one at home.
-I've never slept in a bed.

11:15.250 --> 11:17.333
-Where did you sleep?
-In a hammock.

11:17.417 --> 11:20.083
-Geez, I hate hammocks.
-I'm not a fan either.

11:20.833 --> 11:21.875
Beds are better.

11:23.542 --> 11:25.708
-Were you at your parents'?
-My Grandma's.

11:25.792 --> 11:28.375
And Mr. Reginaldo's. I worked for him.

11:28.458 --> 11:30.542
-Where are you from?
-From far away.

11:31.167 --> 11:32.208
How old are you?

11:34.958 --> 11:36.375
Don't you know?

11:38.083 --> 11:40.583
You really are a hick, aren't you?

11:46.125 --> 11:47.500
What is the magazine about?

11:49.042 --> 11:51.875
-Aviation.
-It must be good to know how to read.

11:52.375 --> 11:54.083
Would you like to go to college?

11:54.583 --> 11:55.833
College…

11:57.167 --> 11:58.917
I won't die in this junkyard.

11:59.000 --> 12:01.208
-College is not for us.
-Bullshit.

12:04.125 --> 12:07.125
We just got 1,100 lbs of copper wire.

12:07.875 --> 12:08.958
You have to strip it.

12:13.208 --> 12:14.042
Look.

12:14.958 --> 12:16.042
You hold it tight…

12:21.292 --> 12:22.125
Watch.

12:22.875 --> 12:24.833
Remove the rubber cover.

12:25.625 --> 12:26.833
Pure copper.

12:27.833 --> 12:29.375
It's worth a lot of money.

12:30.375 --> 12:32.750
Copper goes here, rubber there.

12:35.292 --> 12:36.417
On to stainless steel.

12:37.250 --> 12:38.083
Hold it.

12:40.250 --> 12:41.208
Grab the magnet.

12:45.958 --> 12:48.000
If it doesn't stick, it's worth more.

12:49.167 --> 12:50.250
It goes there.

12:50.333 --> 12:51.375
Is it hard?

12:51.458 --> 12:52.708
-No, sir.
-Ready to work?

12:52.792 --> 12:55.500
-Let's do it!
-Split up and get to work.

12:57.042 --> 12:59.167
Hurry up. The first truck is coming.

13:10.750 --> 13:11.750
Unload the truck!

13:14.708 --> 13:15.542
Come on, son!

13:16.208 --> 13:17.292
No work, no money.

13:29.792 --> 13:30.625
<i>Hi, Mom.</i>

13:30.708 --> 13:32.750
<i>Hi, Mateus. Did you arrive safely?</i>

13:32.833 --> 13:34.458
<i>I did, thank God.</i>

13:34.542 --> 13:36.042
<i>So? How do you like it?</i>

13:36.125 --> 13:39.250
It's a big junkyard, Mom.
There's a lot of work.

13:39.792 --> 13:41.458
<i>No, I meant the city.</i>

13:41.542 --> 13:43.292
We haven't gone out yet.

13:43.375 --> 13:45.208
We'll do something next week.

13:45.292 --> 13:48.583
<i>You must be tired, right, son?</i>
<i>I miss you and…</i>

13:49.625 --> 13:52.542
YOU'RE OUT OF CREDIT
REPLY "1" TO ADD MORE

14:00.542 --> 14:02.458
A pile of scrap for each of you.

14:27.958 --> 14:28.958
Break down the cars.

14:35.792 --> 14:37.875
We've worked the whole week without pay.

14:37.958 --> 14:41.125
-If he gets paid, he has to pay us.
-I'd rather be at home.

14:41.208 --> 14:42.583
I won't work for free.

14:42.667 --> 14:45.292
Don't worry.
If we do our job, he'll pay us.

15:07.750 --> 15:09.500
All right. Yes, sir.

15:11.458 --> 15:14.875
Listen, we have two more deliveries today.
Hurry up.

15:17.333 --> 15:19.375
Our lunch break is not over, Mr. Luca.

15:20.042 --> 15:20.875
Oh, yeah?

15:21.875 --> 15:23.250
Neither are the deliveries.

15:24.375 --> 15:25.917
We're late. What do we do?

15:26.000 --> 15:28.625
We did over 30 deliveries this week
without pay.

15:28.708 --> 15:30.750
Sorry, but I'll finish my lunch.

15:31.292 --> 15:32.917
With all due respect…

15:33.000 --> 15:36.792
When we accepted the job,
Gilson told us we'd get paid per delivery.

15:36.875 --> 15:38.792
We're working overtime without pay.

15:38.875 --> 15:39.833
Didn't you?

15:41.625 --> 15:42.458
How about me?

15:44.542 --> 15:48.917
Who paid your families in advance?
Who's paying for your lodgings?

15:49.750 --> 15:51.958
Food, transport, all your expenses?

15:53.000 --> 15:54.000
Is that cheap?

15:58.042 --> 15:59.375
You will get paid.

15:59.958 --> 16:01.167
Pay what you owe me.

16:01.250 --> 16:03.250
I'll deduct it from the wages.

16:03.333 --> 16:04.375
Nobody told us that.

16:05.375 --> 16:06.792
That's not my problem.

16:06.875 --> 16:08.875
Fuck you and your debt then!

16:11.208 --> 16:12.042
Nando.

16:14.458 --> 16:15.542
That's enough, Nando.

16:19.458 --> 16:20.500
He got the message.

16:22.833 --> 16:24.875
You're lucky I write it all down.

16:32.958 --> 16:34.250
Work and pay it off.

16:35.750 --> 16:36.875
Give me your phone.

16:38.625 --> 16:39.917
Now, dammit!

16:40.000 --> 16:40.833
Give it to me.

16:53.208 --> 16:54.167
I don't have it.

17:21.583 --> 17:23.000
It's for collateral.

17:26.750 --> 17:28.750
$1,000 in advance for each of you.

17:28.833 --> 17:30.333
$5,000 for the recruiter.

17:31.000 --> 17:32.792
$3,000 per month for lodging.

17:32.875 --> 17:34.583
$2,000 for one-way trip.

17:35.125 --> 17:36.667
$700 per month for food.

17:37.292 --> 17:39.292
$200 per month for tools.

17:39.833 --> 17:42.125
And the $20 for food on the first day.

17:42.208 --> 17:44.125
That motherfucking thief!

17:46.458 --> 17:48.500
He spent it on us, we must pay him back.

17:48.583 --> 17:51.333
Is it fair to pay $3,000 a month
for this pigsty?

17:51.417 --> 17:53.333
It pays for a mansion back home.

17:54.292 --> 17:56.000
I always pay my debts.

17:58.000 --> 18:00.792
It's more than our wage.
We'll go to the police.

18:02.500 --> 18:03.375
I can't.

18:04.542 --> 18:05.458
Come on, Ezequiel.

18:05.542 --> 18:07.625
I can't go back empty-handed.

18:10.042 --> 18:11.458
You don't have to go back.

18:12.083 --> 18:13.417
You can stay at my place.

18:13.958 --> 18:15.417
Now, pack up your stuff.

18:42.083 --> 18:42.958
No way out.

18:44.542 --> 18:46.250
I'll check the gate upstairs.

19:12.333 --> 19:13.708
Looking for something?

19:14.458 --> 19:15.958
Where's the key, motherfucker?

19:19.500 --> 19:20.500
Going for a stroll?

19:24.792 --> 19:26.500
Let me make it very clear.

19:28.583 --> 19:29.875
You took a ride here.

19:31.208 --> 19:33.958
I did you a favor, and now you owe me.

19:34.708 --> 19:36.417
What do you do when you owe money?

19:38.750 --> 19:39.875
-Pay.
-You pay.

19:41.458 --> 19:44.833
Back to the fucking dorm.
You'll work tomorrow. Move!

20:03.333 --> 20:05.125
Son of a bitch!

20:11.208 --> 20:12.833
Why did Gilson set us up?

20:12.917 --> 20:15.167
-He didn't know.
-Yes, he did!

20:15.250 --> 20:17.250
He said he knew the guys, it was fine.

20:17.333 --> 20:19.833
-I'll kill that asshole.
-We must get out of here.

20:19.917 --> 20:22.708
We'll jump him
when he comes in tomorrow.

20:22.792 --> 20:25.333
He'll be ready.
Let's do it when the gate is open.

20:25.417 --> 20:27.583
-When a truck arrives.
-He has a gun.

20:27.667 --> 20:29.750
Can we distract him?

20:29.833 --> 20:32.125
It's a waste of time.
Let's jump him tomorrow.

20:32.208 --> 20:34.583
That guy knows what he's doing, Isaque.

20:34.667 --> 20:36.125
We must be smarter than him.

21:09.292 --> 21:10.125
Go.

21:11.542 --> 21:12.583
Cool.

21:15.083 --> 21:16.167
Mr. Luca!

21:17.708 --> 21:19.125
Samuel!

21:20.542 --> 21:21.833
Help him, Mr. Luca!

21:23.375 --> 21:25.375
Call an ambulance. He's dying.

21:26.208 --> 21:27.083
Samuel!

21:28.750 --> 21:30.375
Goddammit!

21:31.792 --> 21:32.708
Bring water.

21:42.875 --> 21:44.458
Stop!

21:44.542 --> 21:45.500
Stop, damn it!

21:45.583 --> 21:47.583
Step back!

21:49.167 --> 21:50.000
Are you crazy?

21:55.708 --> 21:57.042
One escaped, Mr. Luca.

22:47.167 --> 22:48.167
Back in Ariranha,

22:48.917 --> 22:51.500
near the edge of town,
there's a house that's on its own.

22:52.125 --> 22:53.167
It's <i>Dona </i>Ana's.

22:54.167 --> 22:55.792
She lives with her three children.

22:55.875 --> 22:57.625
Odete, Cirlene,

22:57.708 --> 22:58.750
and you, Mateus.

22:59.833 --> 23:00.875
What's up, Samuel?

23:02.500 --> 23:06.167
Your family lives in a stilt house,
near Mr. Geraldo's farm.

23:07.542 --> 23:10.375
You live at number 2,
right by the highway.

23:11.583 --> 23:13.875
Do you know what I hate
in the countryside?

23:14.375 --> 23:16.375
Everything turns into news.

23:17.375 --> 23:20.208
I don't want anyone's mother
to be in the news.

23:22.708 --> 23:24.917
You'd better not even look at Luca.

23:25.000 --> 23:27.250
It'll be worse for your families.

23:38.125 --> 23:39.125
<i>Toothpaste!</i>

23:40.625 --> 23:41.917
It was your idea, right?

23:42.750 --> 23:45.333
Against the wall! Go! Move, damn it!

23:46.417 --> 23:49.000
-Legs apart, damn it!
-You want to act like animals?

23:49.500 --> 23:53.125
We'll treat you like animals.
No shower. No toothpaste.

23:53.208 --> 23:54.208
No dinner.

23:56.833 --> 23:57.667
What?

23:58.417 --> 23:59.417
Wanna eat?

24:01.292 --> 24:02.500
Gotta earn it.

24:04.417 --> 24:05.333
No running away!

24:06.750 --> 24:08.958
Do your job, get the deliveries done.

24:11.125 --> 24:12.708
-How are we?
-We're late.

24:12.792 --> 24:15.333
-How late?
-Six deliveries behind, Mr. Luca.

24:18.292 --> 24:19.250
Get to work!

24:19.792 --> 24:20.917
Yes.

24:22.292 --> 24:24.167
Yes, Mr. Luca.

24:24.250 --> 24:25.792
Thank you, Mr. Luca.

24:25.875 --> 24:27.500
Please, Mr. Luca.

24:27.583 --> 24:29.333
Respect, damn it!

24:30.125 --> 24:31.917
-Yes, Mr. Luca.
-Yes, Mr. Luca.

24:34.833 --> 24:36.250
Have a good day at work.

24:37.792 --> 24:39.292
Move! Now!

24:41.667 --> 24:42.500
Hurry up!

24:44.042 --> 24:45.292
Go on! Get started!

24:46.375 --> 24:47.208
Hurry up!

24:50.042 --> 24:51.417
Stop!

24:53.042 --> 24:53.875
Help!

24:54.792 --> 24:55.625
Hey!

24:56.583 --> 24:57.417
Here!

24:58.625 --> 24:59.500
Try it.

25:00.042 --> 25:02.292
Ask for help. No one will hear you.

25:03.000 --> 25:04.333
But if they do,

25:04.417 --> 25:07.167
my friends will visit your families.

25:09.833 --> 25:11.875
Let's get back to work, shall we?

25:12.375 --> 25:13.292
Get going!

25:37.458 --> 25:39.958
-Shut up, idiot!
-Stop it, Isaque.

25:47.333 --> 25:48.958
That hick will fuck it all up.

25:49.458 --> 25:51.833
Stop whining or I will punch you, pansy.

25:51.917 --> 25:53.083
Let him be.

25:53.167 --> 25:56.000
You missed Luca's head
