53:01.208 --> 53:02.042
The money?

53:02.125 --> 53:05.208
Tell him to come and get it.
I know he wants it.

53:06.208 --> 53:09.125
Luca can come and get it. Leave, now.

53:09.792 --> 53:11.917
It's $10k each. Gimme the money.

53:17.375 --> 53:20.250
Have you lost your mind?
Do you want to get shot?

53:20.333 --> 53:23.917
Are you crazy? Take him out now!
Crazy little shit.

53:24.000 --> 53:26.875
He told me to kill you.
Do you want to die here?

53:28.208 --> 53:31.167
Do it. Luca will kill me
if I don't bring him the money.

53:31.875 --> 53:33.250
But he'll kill you too.

53:34.792 --> 53:35.750
Did you hear me?

53:36.917 --> 53:38.333
Luca will kill us both.

53:43.250 --> 53:45.750
Tell Luca to go fuck himself, little shit!

53:48.542 --> 53:51.000
Stop messing around!
Show some respect! Go!

53:51.958 --> 53:53.083
Get the fuck out!

54:14.000 --> 54:14.833
I'm listening.

54:20.458 --> 54:22.167
Bro, who's gonna pay?

54:23.125 --> 54:24.833
Who's gonna pay?

54:43.292 --> 54:45.375
-Okay.
-Mr. Luca.

54:54.208 --> 54:55.292
How much do you want?

54:56.500 --> 54:57.333
Say it.

54:58.375 --> 54:59.208
Half.

55:01.000 --> 55:02.000
Ten grand?

55:10.542 --> 55:12.083
This is the boss's cut.

55:12.667 --> 55:14.667
-Five hundred.
-One grand.

55:26.292 --> 55:27.625
How did they get here?

55:29.000 --> 55:31.458
By plane, bus, ship.

55:32.792 --> 55:34.083
Like everything we buy.

55:35.792 --> 55:36.917
How many are there?

55:41.667 --> 55:43.583
Enough to keep the city running.

55:46.500 --> 55:47.458
Do you see that?

55:48.333 --> 55:50.167
Copper wire from our junkyard.

55:52.833 --> 55:53.708
Look.

55:53.792 --> 55:55.625
That's your work all over town.

56:51.833 --> 56:52.667
Come on.

56:57.292 --> 56:58.417
Get him out of there.

57:03.708 --> 57:05.958
Sir, please, don't hurt him.

57:07.083 --> 57:08.083
He's just scared.

57:28.167 --> 57:29.000
Go.

57:46.000 --> 57:47.125
You sleep here now.

57:49.792 --> 57:50.792
There's no need.

57:52.167 --> 57:54.375
He'll stab you in the eye
when you're asleep.

57:57.750 --> 57:58.750
I'm sure of that.

57:59.750 --> 58:01.500
How long have you been doing it?

58:02.000 --> 58:03.042
Long enough.

58:04.542 --> 58:05.958
Has anyone ever escaped?

58:09.042 --> 58:10.000
Not from me.

58:11.708 --> 58:13.458
Let's see how it goes with you.

58:18.875 --> 58:21.792
Mr. Luca, thanks for all this,
but I can't.

58:23.375 --> 58:24.208
Why is that?

58:28.417 --> 58:29.542
I won't do it.

58:30.583 --> 58:32.542
I won't keep them captive or hurt them.

58:36.000 --> 58:36.833
Okay.

58:38.417 --> 58:39.250
Go back, then.

58:39.875 --> 58:40.708
Go.

58:42.542 --> 58:43.750
Go back to your friends.

58:44.875 --> 58:46.375
Someone else will do it.

58:50.750 --> 58:52.583
I don't know how you can do it.

58:54.917 --> 58:56.167
You're doing it too.

58:56.833 --> 58:58.250
Not because I want to.

58:58.917 --> 59:01.042
We have a deal. After that, I'm free.

59:01.125 --> 59:01.958
Free?

59:04.542 --> 59:05.500
To do what?

59:07.417 --> 59:08.250
Starve?

59:09.667 --> 59:11.292
See your family live in squalor?

59:11.958 --> 59:13.208
I saw your magazines.

59:15.333 --> 59:16.625
You wanted to be a pilot?

59:17.375 --> 59:18.667
-Engineer.
-Nice.

59:20.917 --> 59:22.292
Important job.

59:23.042 --> 59:24.167
I wanted that too.

59:25.500 --> 59:27.458
Why don't you do something else, then?

59:35.667 --> 59:37.583
I came from a shithole, just like you.

59:38.833 --> 59:41.125
Raised in a shack next to an open sewer.

59:41.917 --> 59:45.292
My mom worked her ass off
to provide for four kids. Alone.

59:46.750 --> 59:49.250
Her boss, a very good man,

59:49.333 --> 59:50.708
treated us like family.

59:52.833 --> 59:55.292
But he'd force her to work 12 hours a day

59:55.375 --> 59:56.792
and paid $600 a month.

59:57.917 --> 1:00:00.000
The fucker's shoes cost more than that.

1:00:03.708 --> 1:00:05.333
Is that the freedom you want?

1:00:10.167 --> 1:00:11.167
There's the door.

1:00:13.583 --> 1:00:14.667
Go, be free.

1:01:14.542 --> 1:01:16.167
Look who showed up.

1:01:18.792 --> 1:01:20.542
Will you take us out of here?

1:01:20.625 --> 1:01:21.750
Open this shit!

1:01:22.667 --> 1:01:23.875
Did you choose them?

1:01:24.667 --> 1:01:25.625
Say it.

1:01:25.708 --> 1:01:27.667
Yes, he brought me here.

1:01:27.750 --> 1:01:29.375
Are you a badass now?

1:01:30.542 --> 1:01:33.542
-Do you know how to use that shit?
-Get back, Isaque.

1:01:37.875 --> 1:01:38.792
Come, Samuel.

1:01:46.500 --> 1:01:47.458
He's out there.

1:01:48.250 --> 1:01:49.333
Help me with them.

1:01:50.083 --> 1:01:52.125
I'm doing my best to get us out of here.

1:01:58.250 --> 1:01:59.083
Move!

1:02:00.958 --> 1:02:02.458
Open it, everybody out.

1:02:06.667 --> 1:02:07.500
Let's go.

1:02:09.458 --> 1:02:10.292
Go, faster!

1:02:48.875 --> 1:02:49.708
Pure copper.

1:02:50.667 --> 1:02:52.667
Copper goes here, rubber there.

1:02:53.208 --> 1:02:54.042
Got it?

1:03:04.875 --> 1:03:06.958
You have to move this shit, not me.

1:03:07.500 --> 1:03:09.000
Get to work. Hurry up.

1:03:53.042 --> 1:03:54.750
<i>Do you guys need anything?</i>

1:03:55.292 --> 1:03:57.208
Isaque was right about you.

1:03:57.292 --> 1:03:58.542
I didn't choose this.

1:03:59.500 --> 1:04:01.375
What should I do? Tell him I can't?

1:04:02.042 --> 1:04:02.875
Yes.

1:04:03.458 --> 1:04:05.708
You'd rather have him watching us?

1:04:06.375 --> 1:04:07.542
I'm one of you.

1:04:09.250 --> 1:04:10.958
I can talk to your family.

1:04:11.625 --> 1:04:13.833
I can call your mom. Julia.

1:04:15.083 --> 1:04:18.042
-I'll talk to the others.
-To who? Isaque?

1:04:20.875 --> 1:04:22.000
Forget him, Samuel.

1:04:22.958 --> 1:04:24.375
He'll make things worse.

1:04:25.000 --> 1:04:26.333
We're from the same place.

1:04:27.792 --> 1:04:28.625
Okay.

1:04:29.917 --> 1:04:31.042
And the deal?

1:04:33.250 --> 1:04:35.167
I can get us out of here even earlier.

1:04:51.333 --> 1:04:52.333
You'll need this.

1:04:53.667 --> 1:04:55.917
I added my number, Nando's and Batista's.

1:04:58.625 --> 1:05:00.167
You can call your mom too.

1:05:03.208 --> 1:05:04.333
Go ahead, call her.

1:05:17.042 --> 1:05:18.500
<i>-Hello?</i>
-Mom?

1:05:18.583 --> 1:05:20.458
<i>Mateus? Where are you?</i>

1:05:20.542 --> 1:05:22.917
<i>I've been trying to call,</i>
<i>but you didn't answer.</i>

1:05:23.458 --> 1:05:26.292
This is my new number, Mom.
I forgot to tell you.

1:05:26.792 --> 1:05:30.417
<i>How can you disappear?</i>
<i>You send money and don't say anything?</i>

1:05:31.292 --> 1:05:32.250
What money, Mom?

1:05:32.875 --> 1:05:35.208
<i>The money you sent me, son.</i>

1:05:35.292 --> 1:05:37.333
<i>How did you make that much money?</i>

1:05:39.417 --> 1:05:41.333
I've been doing some extra work.

1:05:41.417 --> 1:05:43.000
<i>How are the other boys?</i>

1:05:44.875 --> 1:05:47.375
-They're fine, thank God.
<i>-Call me again.</i>

1:05:47.458 --> 1:05:49.125
<i>We miss you.</i>

1:05:49.208 --> 1:05:50.042
I will, Mom.

1:05:50.625 --> 1:05:52.333
-Bye.
<i>-Call me.</i>

1:05:58.375 --> 1:05:59.833
I sent her $4,000.

1:06:02.542 --> 1:06:03.625
You've earned it.

1:06:05.042 --> 1:06:06.583
That's just the beginning.

1:06:30.125 --> 1:06:32.708
-Drink it. I'm buying.
-It's really good.

1:06:33.417 --> 1:06:34.250
Look.

1:06:35.250 --> 1:06:36.750
-Hey!
-Sorry, sir.

1:06:36.833 --> 1:06:39.458
-Do you make him call you "sir"?
-So what?

1:06:40.375 --> 1:06:41.792
Is that how you talk to him?

1:06:42.583 --> 1:06:44.292
You must control him, got it?

1:06:44.375 --> 1:06:45.750
Yes, I will.

1:06:46.417 --> 1:06:48.833
What did you do
in the countryside for fun?

1:06:49.875 --> 1:06:52.833
-Give me a cigarette.
-Cool. I like that.

1:06:52.917 --> 1:06:53.750
Here.

1:07:04.750 --> 1:07:05.875
A beer, please.

1:07:23.000 --> 1:07:25.917
So? You must bring your mom
to meet her daughter-in-law.

1:07:28.000 --> 1:07:30.417
-Mom wouldn't get used to São Paulo.
-Really?

1:07:31.625 --> 1:07:32.875
Will you leave her there?

1:07:33.375 --> 1:07:34.625
She'd want to say.

1:07:35.458 --> 1:07:37.500
But she must quit working,
or she'll die.

1:07:37.583 --> 1:07:40.292
-I don't know how she does it.
-And your father?

1:07:41.292 --> 1:07:42.125
Father?

1:07:43.417 --> 1:07:45.458
When I have kids, I'll be a good father.

1:07:45.958 --> 1:07:47.458
Do you want kids?

1:07:47.542 --> 1:07:48.375
Four.

1:07:49.250 --> 1:07:50.458
Two girls, two boys.

1:07:51.292 --> 1:07:54.542
You'll take care of your kids,
your mom, everything.

1:08:04.500 --> 1:08:05.875
Cheers!

1:09:09.375 --> 1:09:11.083
Get us some beers, will you?

1:09:27.875 --> 1:09:28.708
Mr. Luca…

1:09:32.542 --> 1:09:33.375
Mr. Luca?

1:09:34.208 --> 1:09:35.042
Mr. Luca?

1:11:42.250 --> 1:11:44.375
Eat it before he sees it.

1:11:49.042 --> 1:11:50.333
Did you have a fun night?

1:11:50.833 --> 1:11:53.625
Where's Luca?
Does he let you come and go now?

1:11:54.708 --> 1:11:58.000
-Where's Luca? Answer me, damn it!
-He's right there.

1:11:58.792 --> 1:12:01.167
-In the office.
-The asshole must've passed out.

1:12:01.250 --> 1:12:03.875
This one left a free man,

1:12:03.958 --> 1:12:05.625
and came back a free man.

1:12:05.708 --> 1:12:06.625
Is that true?

1:12:07.458 --> 1:12:08.458
Answer, Mateus.

1:12:11.875 --> 1:12:14.167
Eat, we have work to do. Hurry up.

1:13:01.750 --> 1:13:02.583
Okay.

1:13:29.167 --> 1:13:31.792
-Sing something.
-Sing, Samuel.

1:13:40.833 --> 1:13:44.125
BIANCHI = FUTURE

1:13:45.000 --> 1:13:46.250
What's up, Big Luca?

1:13:47.583 --> 1:13:49.167
-How are you?
-I'm fine.

1:14:04.208 --> 1:14:05.333
Let me take a look.

1:14:06.833 --> 1:14:08.208
All right, legs apart.

1:14:27.000 --> 1:14:29.083
-Excuse me.
-Hey.

1:14:30.125 --> 1:14:32.250
-How are you?
-Hi, Luca. How are you?

1:14:35.042 --> 1:14:37.000
A gift for your daughter, Mr. Bianchi.

1:14:37.500 --> 1:14:38.750
You shouldn't have.

1:14:39.417 --> 1:14:40.250
Take it inside.

1:14:40.333 --> 1:14:41.667
-Thank you.
-Sit down.

1:14:45.875 --> 1:14:47.083
Get Rodiney for me.

1:14:49.958 --> 1:14:51.042
Here's the deal.

1:14:51.125 --> 1:14:53.458
I have to focus on my campaign.

1:14:53.542 --> 1:14:55.333
I'll give you the office keys.

1:14:55.833 --> 1:14:57.625
You're out of the junkyard.

1:14:57.708 --> 1:15:00.042
I want you out on the front line
of the business.

1:15:01.750 --> 1:15:04.083
You'll do the rounds day and night,

1:15:04.167 --> 1:15:06.958
check productivity, schedule workers.

1:15:07.042 --> 1:15:08.667
Then you report back to me.

1:15:10.292 --> 1:15:11.500
You can count on me.

1:15:14.792 --> 1:15:16.583
Look, this is Rodiney.

1:15:17.167 --> 1:15:19.083
He'll take over the junkyard.

1:15:19.708 --> 1:15:20.583
Cool.

1:15:21.083 --> 1:15:22.208
No more easy life.

1:15:23.125 --> 1:15:24.750
That's it. Enjoy the party.

1:15:32.208 --> 1:15:34.292
-Hi. How are you?
-How are you?

1:15:34.375 --> 1:15:38.917
There's a song by Noel Rosa I like a lot
called "Fita Amarela". Do you know it?

1:15:39.000 --> 1:15:41.417
-So…
-"Fita Amalera." I mean, "Fita Amarela."

1:15:49.875 --> 1:15:51.083
Don't move.

1:15:51.167 --> 1:15:52.750
Hey, what are you doing?

1:15:53.833 --> 1:15:55.500
-There's no one here.
-Right.

1:15:56.000 --> 1:15:59.375
Go play with your friends.
Tell Cida to hide in the kitchen.

1:15:59.875 --> 1:16:00.708
Goodness…

1:16:00.792 --> 1:16:02.417
-Your daughter?
-Yeah.

1:16:03.125 --> 1:16:05.042
-Do you like kids?
-I do, sir.

1:16:05.125 --> 1:16:07.833
I got into politics because of them.

1:16:07.917 --> 1:16:10.500
I want to make this country
a better place for them.

1:16:10.583 --> 1:16:12.667
-You're with Luca, right?
-Yes.

1:16:13.167 --> 1:16:15.167
-Have you known him a long time?
-Yes.

1:16:15.250 --> 1:16:17.583
My father had businesses in Itaquera.

1:16:18.167 --> 1:16:20.583
I ended up taking over the businesses,

1:16:20.667 --> 1:16:23.750
and I needed someone
to bring me food and stuff, right?

1:16:24.250 --> 1:16:25.250
Then I saw him.

1:16:25.792 --> 1:16:27.708
He stood out from the others.

1:16:28.917 --> 1:16:31.167
I just needed to whistle like this…

1:16:36.250 --> 1:16:37.458
Been with me ever since.

1:16:50.458 --> 1:16:52.500
Those people we bought, they work for him?

1:16:59.583 --> 1:17:01.500
Has anyone got a deal like ours?

1:17:04.542 --> 1:17:05.667
You got lucky, kid.

1:17:09.083 --> 1:17:10.417
I mean, the other guys.

1:17:15.708 --> 1:17:16.542
No deal?

1:17:21.125 --> 1:17:22.958
Won't they get out once they pay up?

1:17:30.542 --> 1:17:32.500
Next week, I'm leaving the junkyard.

1:17:33.125 --> 1:17:35.125
If you want a promotion, there's a spot.

1:17:37.333 --> 1:17:38.500
Otherwise, stay there.

1:17:40.417 --> 1:17:41.333
It's up to you.

1:18:24.500 --> 1:18:26.250
That was the issue…

1:18:33.167 --> 1:18:35.875
Your beard is getting grayer, son.

1:18:36.917 --> 1:18:37.958
Who is this one?

1:18:40.167 --> 1:18:42.542
He works with me. Mateus.

1:18:43.125 --> 1:18:45.083
-So young?
-Not as young as you, ma'am.

1:18:45.833 --> 1:18:48.750
-Pleasure to meet you.
-A silver-tongued boy, huh?

1:18:49.833 --> 1:18:51.958
-No need for "ma'am."
-Off to the restroom.

1:18:52.042 --> 1:18:53.667
Okay. Your siblings are coming.

1:18:53.750 --> 1:18:57.333
It's a miracle he showed up.
He works so hard.

1:18:57.417 --> 1:18:59.500
But he shows up once in a while!

1:18:59.583 --> 1:19:02.208
Help him get in good spirits.

1:19:02.292 --> 1:19:04.667
-It's a lost cause.
-Look who's coming.

1:19:04.750 --> 1:19:06.917
-There she is.
-Hello.

1:19:07.000 --> 1:19:08.083
Thanks, Edileuza.

1:19:08.167 --> 1:19:10.292
-There you go!
-Enjoy.

1:19:10.375 --> 1:19:12.333
That's not how I raised you.

1:19:12.417 --> 1:19:14.792
Guests first. Go ahead.

1:19:14.875 --> 1:19:17.000
You'll eat the best coxinha ever.

1:19:17.083 --> 1:19:19.542
This is what keeps
this place running. Here.

1:19:19.625 --> 1:19:20.750
-Wait for it…
-Eat it.

1:19:23.458 --> 1:19:24.292
Tears of joy!

1:19:25.500 --> 1:19:26.333
Am I right?

1:19:26.958 --> 1:19:29.958
He keeps this place running.
He bought the bakery for me.

1:19:30.042 --> 1:19:32.458
How many moms can say that? I can.

1:19:32.542 --> 1:19:34.333
So? How's Ana?

1:19:34.417 --> 1:19:37.875
Tell him, Mazinho. She doesn't want kids.

1:19:37.958 --> 1:19:40.375
-Bitch.
-Mom, let him be. Forget it.

1:19:40.458 --> 1:19:43.875
-I do, but she doesn't.
-Soon you'll be surrounded by grandkids.

1:19:43.958 --> 1:19:45.333
-Really? I will?
-No.

1:19:45.417 --> 1:19:47.792
Where are they? Bring me my grandkids.

1:19:48.292 --> 1:19:50.417
-They're hiding.
-I'll look for one.

1:19:51.333 --> 1:19:53.833
Moms just want
what's best for their kids.

1:19:54.625 --> 1:19:58.042
I want the best for them.
Doesn't your mom want that, too?

1:19:58.125 --> 1:19:59.792
Exactly. What does she do?

1:19:59.875 --> 1:20:01.417
She works in the fields.

1:20:01.500 --> 1:20:03.167
I did that for a long time.

1:20:03.250 --> 1:20:05.250
-Are you from the countryside?
-No.

1:20:05.333 --> 1:20:08.083
We lived in Rio, in the middle of nowhere.

1:20:09.042 --> 1:20:10.375
Up on a slope.

1:20:10.458 --> 1:20:14.792
We came to São Paulo when Luca
was a teenager, 13, 14 years old.

1:20:15.583 --> 1:20:17.583
Was he a handful?

1:20:17.667 --> 1:20:19.083
No, not Luca.

1:20:20.125 --> 1:20:22.250
Luca was never afraid of anything.

1:20:22.333 --> 1:20:24.583
He used to steal the boss's horses,

1:20:25.625 --> 1:20:27.500
run away in the middle of the night.

1:20:27.583 --> 1:20:29.167
He sold the boss's chickens,

1:20:29.250 --> 1:20:31.042
but he never lied to me. Ever.

1:20:31.125 --> 1:20:33.417
He always brought home the money.

1:20:34.208 --> 1:20:35.458
A golden boy.

1:20:35.542 --> 1:20:38.958
He was born to be a leader.
Whatever he says is the law.

1:20:39.042 --> 1:20:41.083
Stand by him and you'll do well.

1:20:42.083 --> 1:20:43.292
So, you were a peasant?

1:20:44.250 --> 1:20:47.750
No, that's not… I didn't say that.

1:20:47.833 --> 1:20:51.083
-One beer and you're tipsy?
-No, that's a lie!

1:20:51.167 --> 1:20:54.125
-I didn't say that.
-All right.

1:20:54.208 --> 1:20:55.083
Give me some.

1:21:14.792 --> 1:21:17.625
There's a shipment next week.
Copper wire and stainless steel.

1:21:17.708 --> 1:21:19.667
-Got it.
-You can come and get it.

1:21:20.417 --> 1:21:21.958
Hey, look!

1:21:22.042 --> 1:21:23.375
-Grab him!
-Get him!

1:21:23.458 --> 1:21:25.292
-Luca!
-Luca!

1:21:25.375 --> 1:21:27.083
The guy escaped!

1:22:37.958 --> 1:22:39.167
Call Batista.

1:22:43.917 --> 1:22:45.083
Show him the picture.

1:22:46.917 --> 1:22:48.042
It's not necessary.

1:22:55.667 --> 1:22:56.750
It's them or us.

1:22:57.625 --> 1:22:58.458
Make the call.

1:23:18.292 --> 1:23:20.000
<i>-Who is it?</i>
-Mateus.

1:23:20.542 --> 1:23:22.417
<i>What's up? What do you need?</i>

1:23:22.500 --> 1:23:25.125
-One of the guys tried to run away.
<i>-Who?</i>

1:23:25.958 --> 1:23:28.042
-Samuel.
<i>-What do you want?</i>

1:23:28.833 --> 1:23:30.125
Stop by his house.

1:23:30.208 --> 1:23:31.333
<i>Should I be rough?</i>

1:23:32.292 --> 1:23:33.125
No.

1:23:34.125 --> 1:23:35.292
Give them a scare.

1:24:04.000 --> 1:24:08.875
TELL SAMUEL
HIS MOTHER SAYS HI

1:24:18.583 --> 1:24:19.667
Say "Portuguese."

1:24:21.000 --> 1:24:21.917
Portuguese.

1:24:30.208 --> 1:24:31.167
I didn't want this.

1:25:07.458 --> 1:25:10.625
The truck comes five times a day.
We're making 15 deliveries.

1:25:11.125 --> 1:25:12.250
We can do more.

1:25:13.250 --> 1:25:15.042
Who tried to escape?

1:25:18.125 --> 1:25:18.958
That one.

1:25:22.292 --> 1:25:23.667
I thought there were seven.

1:25:26.708 --> 1:25:27.833
That's all of them.

1:25:30.458 --> 1:25:33.542
Tuesdays and Thursdays are busy.
You'll have to run inventory.

1:25:38.833 --> 1:25:40.167
Take your lunch break.

1:25:43.792 --> 1:25:45.083
Do you have a cigarette?

1:25:51.417 --> 1:25:52.417
I need a lighter.

1:26:20.000 --> 1:26:21.958
Yeah. We'll see.

1:26:23.958 --> 1:26:25.667
-You got everything?
-Yes.

1:33:16.917 --> 1:33:21.917
Subtitle translation by:
Carla Tessaro
